    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <head>No. 66.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herbert</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 5, 1888</date>. (Received December
                        5.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the case of the seizure of four
                    British sealing ships in Behring Sea, I have the honor to inclose, for
                    convenience of reference, copy of Lord Sackville’s dispatch of October 12<note
                        n="*" xml:id="d521fn1">See <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>, No. 57.</note>
                    (without its inclosure) to your Department, as I have been instructed by the
                    Marquis of Salisbury to call your attention to the fact that up to the present
                    no answer has been received, and to beg the favor of an early reply.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur Herbert</hi>
                    </signed>,<lb/>For <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">M. H. Herbert.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
